Full job description

About the Role

We are seeking a seasoned Senior Software Developer to join our dynamic team. With over 5+ years of experience in full-stack development, specialising in Node.js, Nest.js, and Python, you will be instrumental in building and optimizing our cutting-edge web applications and platforms. Your role extends to designing microservices architecture and contributing to projects with a keen interest in Artificial Intelligence. As a leader, you will guide and mentor a team of developers, fostering an environment of growth and innovation.

About Launchpad

Launchpad is a collective of experienced developers and designers committed to crafting superior software solutions for businesses of varying scales. Our company stands at the forefront of technology, delivering bespoke software solutions that drive efficiency, growth, and engagement. We pride ourselves on our agile approach, user-centric design, and commitment to excellence. Joining us means becoming part of a passionate team that believes in pushing boundaries, continuous learning, and making a positive impact through technology.

Join Our Team

Embark on a thrilling journey in tech with us as a Lead Backend Engineer. At Launchpad, you are exposed to the forefront of technological evolution, engage with a skilled and diverse team, and significantly influence our offerings. We offer a unique opportunity to contribute to exciting projects, develop your skills, and advance your career in a vibrant and supportive environment.

Responsibilities

  • Architectural Excellence & Scalability: Architect and develop scalable backend systems, employing Node.js, Nest.js, Python, and microservices, grounded in fundamental design principles for scalability and performance.
  • Code Security & Reusability: Build secure, efficient, and reusable code and libraries, ensuring the security and maintainability of our applications.
  • Code Review & Quality Assurance: Lead effective code reviews, validating and correcting upstream technical designs to uphold high standards of code quality and functionality.
  • Technical Design & Architecture: Write technical designs and contribute to architectural decisions, ensuring alignment with business requirements and scalability needs.
  • Data Modeling & Performance: Apply data modeling techniques to optimize integration and performance, ensuring robustness and efficiency of backend services.
  • Team Leadership & Mentorship: Mentor and manage a team of backend developers, promoting best practices, innovation, and a high standard of code quality. Foster an environment of growth and continuous improvement.
  • Microservices Architecture: Spearhead the development of microservices, ensuring they are modular, scalable, and integrated efficiently within our ecosystem.
  • Feature Demonstration & Estimation: Take responsibility for feature demos and accurately estimate features and tasks, facilitating clear communication and project planning.
  • Technical Strategy & Decision Making: Contribute to technical strategy and decision-making, assessing and adopting new technologies and tools to enhance our backend capabilities.
  • Collaboration & Problem Solving: Work closely with cross-functional teams to understand requirements and deliver solutions that meet or exceed expectations. Utilise exceptional problem-solving skills to overcome technical challenges.
  • Continuous Learning & Innovation: Keep abreast of the latest backend technologies and methodologies, incorporating them into our projects to maintain our competitive edge.

Qualifications

  • Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field.
  • A minimum of 5 years of experience in backend development, with a proven track record in Node.js, Nest.js, Python, and designing microservices architectures.
  • Deep understanding of server-side languages and frameworks, with a focus on Node.js and Python.
  • Experience with database management systems, both SQL and NoSQL.
  • Familiarity with cloud services (GCP), API design principles, and microservices patterns.
  • Proficiency in containerization and orchestration technologies (Docker, Kubernetes) is highly desirable.
  • Demonstrated ability to lead and mentor a team, fostering innovation and technical excellence.
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment.
  • Excellent communication skills, capable of effectively collaborating with cross-functional teams and stakeholders.

Benefits @ Launchpad

Joining Launchpad means being part of a recognised Great Place to Work:

  • Kit Kat Days: Enjoy a 9-day fortnight, because we value work-life balance.
  • Slice of the pie: Shares in Launchpad’s growth and success are available to all.
  • Professional Development & Training Opportunities: We’re committed to your growth and career trajectory.
  • Get a slice of the action: Earn your salary plus a share in the company’s profits.
  • Leading software & tools: Access state-of-the-art software packages and tools.
  • Social enterprise programs: Engage in meaningful projects that benefit the community and environment.
  • Build awesome stuff: Our projects aren’t just work—they’re passion projects.

Job Types: Full-time, Regular / Permanent

  • Hybrid - Bengaluru, India

Supplemental pay types:

  • Quarterly bonus

Inclusion and Diversity

Launchpad is an Equal Opportunity Employer where inclusion matters. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, colour, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.

We expect all employees to live and breathe our behaviours: to act with humility and build trust; lead with transparency; deliver with focus, and drive ownership – always with unyielding integrity.

Our total rewards are designed to unlock your ambition by giving you the boost and flexibility you need to turn your ideas into world-changing realities. Our salary and benefits are everything you’d expect from an organisation with global strength and scale, and you’ll be surrounded by career opportunities in a culture that fosters care, collaboration, and support.
